msgid "rcl - ``rcl_init`` API Change"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Crystal-Clemmys.rst:218
msgid ""
"Like the ``rmw`` change above, there's two new structs in ``rcl`` called "
"``rcl_context_t`` and ``rcl_init_options_t``. The init options are passed "
"into ``rcl_init`` as an input and the context is passed in as an output. The "
"context is used to associate all other rcl entities to a specific init-"
"shutdown cycle, effectively making init and shutdown no longer global "
"functions, or rather those functions no longer use an global state and "
"instead encapsulate all state within the context type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Crystal-Clemmys.rst:222
msgid ""
"Any maintainers of a client library implementation (that also uses ``rcl`` "
"under the hood) will need to make changes to work with Crystal."
msgstr ""

