#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Crystal-Clemmys.rst:266
msgid "Known Issues"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Crystal-Clemmys.rst:268
msgid ""
"A race condition in Fast-RTPS 1.7.0 may cause messages to drop under stress "
"(`Issue <https://github.com/ros2/rmw_fastrtps/issues/258>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Crystal-Clemmys.rst:269
msgid ""
"Using the TRANSIENT_LOCAL QoS setting with rmw_fastrtps_cpp can crash "
"applications with large messages (`Issue <https://github.com/ros2/"
"rmw_fastrtps/issues/257>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Crystal-Clemmys.rst:270
msgid ""
"Cross-vendor communication between rmw_fastrtps_cpp and other "
"implementations is not functioning on Windows (`Issue <https://github.com/"
"ros2/rmw_fastrtps/issues/246>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Crystal-Clemmys.rst:271
msgid ""
"When using OpenSplice (version < 6.9.190227) on macOS and Windows you might "
"experience naming conflicts when when referencing field types with names "
"from other packages if the same name also exist in the current package "
"(`Issue <https://github.com/ros2/rmw_opensplice/issues/259>`__). By updating "
"to a newer OpenSplice version as well as at least the third patch release of "
"Crystal the problem should be resolved. On Linux updating to the latest "
"Debian packages will include the newest OpenSplice version."
msgstr ""
